This permits the use of the new title as a secondary name. Pete Hegseth will be known as the secretary of war. Pentagon websites and signage will also be updated. Trump mentioned the history of victory associated with the department of war.
title: WH pushes 'warrior ethos': Trump revives 'dept of war'; Hegseth gets new title

author: MEGHNA DHULIA
description: Delhi University (DU) continues its dominance in the NIRF 2025 rankings, securing top positions with 32 colleges on the list. Hindu College and Miranda House retain their top spots, while DU achieves its best-ever fifth position among universities. Other Delhi institutions like JNU and Jamia Millia Islamia also shine, with AIIMS Delhi leading in medical and dental categories.
title: NIRF rankings 2025: Hindu, Miranda House remain best two colleges of India

author: SIDHARTHA
description: Following the government's GST rate reductions on numerous goods and services, Indian companies are adjusting prices to benefit consumers by September 22. FMCG firms may increase product quantity for fixed-price items. White goods companies anticipate a demand surge, while hotels offer reduced rates for check-in payments. Car dealers, however, face potential losses due to existing inventory and revised cess structures.
title: Govt revamps GST: Rates reduced on nearly 400 goods — Here’s how cuts will reach consumers by Sept 22

author: AMIT BHATTACHARYA
description: North India experienced unprecedented rainfall between August 22 and September 4, with nearly three times the normal amount. This intense spell, the wettest in at least 14 years, triggered devastating floods in Punjab, record Yamuna levels in Delhi, and landslides in the Himalayas.
title: Battered North India logs its rainiest 2-week period in 14 years

author: PRIYANKA KAKODKAR
description: Maharashtra CM Devendra Fadnavis reached out to Chhagan Bhujbal, addressing OBC concerns over a government resolution regarding Maratha reservations. Bhujbal, after skipping a cabinet meeting, expressed apprehension that the GR could lead to blanket reservations for Marathas via Kunbi certificates.
title: Maratha quota storm: Fadnavis dials Chhagan Bhujbal after cabinet no-show

author: ANURAG BENDE
description: Maharashtra's Deputy Chief Minister Ajit Pawar faces accusations of obstructing IPS officer Anjana Krishna's efforts to curb illegal sand mining in Solapur. A video circulating online purportedly captures Pawar instructing Krishna to halt action against an NCP member involved. Opposition leaders are demanding an apology, alleging Pawar threatened the officer after she insisted on verifying his identity.
title: 'Phone call' halts mining crackdown: Trouble for Ajit Pawar over ‘threat’ to cop?

author: TIMES NEWS NETWORK
description: Rishi Nair, a 19-year-old BITS Pilani Goa student from Bengaluru, was found dead in his hostel room, marking the fifth student death in ten months. Police report Rishi was battling depression following his girlfriend's suicide. His parents had moved him to the Goa campus for support.
title: 5th death in 10 months: BITS Pilani Goa student found dead on campus
